GateDocument.TextWithNodes: Workshop on Management of Semistructured Data - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Friday , May 16 , 1997 Ventana Canyon Resort , Tucson , Arizona In conjunction with PODS / SIGMOD CALL FOR PAPERS and ATTENDANCE - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Recently we have seen an increased interest in managing data that does not easily conform to a conventional relational or object-oriented schema . The reasons for the emergence of such "semistructured" data are diverse , ranging from the integration of heterogeneous data sources to new database applications such as biology databases or the World- Wide- Web . The purpose of this workshop is to bring together researchers interested in the design , implementation , and use of systems designed to manage semistructured data . The topics of interest include , but are not limited to : data models , query languages , object integration and correspondence , data loading , data conversion , and implementation techniques ranging from storage management to query decomposition and processing . The workshop will be rather informal and will encourage discussion and interaction . We invite submissions of short papers ( 5 pages or less ) covering topics related to the management of semistructured data . An informal proceedings will be published , and there will be a registration fee of $ 50 .
